  "prompt": "What apps can be used to put two pictures together?",
  "response": "There are several apps and tools you can use to combine or merge two pictures:\n\n1. Mobile Apps:\n- PicsArt\n- Canva\n- Photo Collage Maker\n- Layout from Instagram\n- Pixlr\n- Photoshop Express\n- PhotoGrid\n\n2. Desktop/Web Applications:\n- Photoshop\n- GIMP (free)\n- Canva (web-based)\n- Fotor\n- Paint.NET\n- Online Photo Editor\n\n3. Smartphone Built-in Features:\n- iPhone: Photos app (create collages)\n- Android: Google Photos\n- Samsung Gallery\n\n4. Free Online Tools:\n- Photopea\n- Pixlr Editor\n- Photocollage.com\n- Befunky\n- Fotor\n\n5. Specific Purpose Apps:\n- Collage apps (for creating photo grids)\n- Side-by-side photo merger apps\n- Split screen photo apps\n\nThe best choice depends on your specific needs, device, and whether you want a simple merge or a more complex edit.",
